{{EngvarB|date=November 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2014}} {{Infobox civilian attack |title=Kogi prison break |partof=[[Boko Haram insurgency]] |image= Nigeria Kogi State map.png |fatalities = 1 |injuries = 0 |type= [[Prison escape|Prison break]] |perps=[[Boko Haram]] |target= |numparts=Unknown |dfens=144 prisoners escaped |date= 02 November 2014 |location=[[Kogi State]], North-central [[Nigeria]] }} {{Campaignbox Boko Haram insurgency}}
The '''Kogi prison break''' was an attack on Koto-Karffi Federal Medium Security Prisons in [[Kogi State]], in north-central [[Nigeria]] by unknown gunmen suspected to be members of the terrorist group, [[Boko Haram|boko haram]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-17059895|title=BBC News - Nigeria jailbreak: Boko Haram claims Kogi prison attack|work=BBC News|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> The attack occurred on 2 November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/boko-haram-invades-kogi-prison-frees-143/ |title=Boko Haram invades Kogi prison, frees 143 |work=The Punch - Nigeria's Most Widely Read Newspaper |accessdate=24 December 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141209145849/http://www.punchng.com/news/boko-haram-invades-kogi-prison-frees-143/ |archivedate= 9 December 2014 |df= }}</ref> About 144 prisoners escaped from the prison leaving 1 inmate dead at gun shot during the attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/top-news/170512-jailbreak-in-kogi-gunmen-free-144-inmates.html|title=Jailbreak in Kogi; gunmen free 144 inmates - Premium Times Nigeria|work=Premium Times Nigeria|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> It was reported that the escaped prisoners were largely awaiting trial for [[robbery]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.today.ng/news/kogi-jailbreak-update-12-escaped-inmates-re-arrested-prison-service/ |title=KOGI JAILBREAK UPDATE: 12 escaped inmates re-arrested – Prison service |work=TODAY |accessdate=24 December 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224170142/http://www.today.ng/news/kogi-jailbreak-update-12-escaped-inmates-re-arrested-prison-service/ |archivedate=24 December 2014 |df= }}</ref> Twelve inmates returned to the prison to serve out their short sentence<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailypost.ng/2014/11/03/kogi-jail-break-12-inmates-re-arrested/|title=Kogi jail break: 12 inmates re-arrested|work=DailyPost Nigeria|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> and about 45 escaped prisoners were recaptured altogether.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thenationonlineng.net/new/kogi-jail-break-45-fleeing-inmates-recaptured/|title=Kogi jail break: 45 fleeing inmates recaptured|author=Gbenga Omokhunu, Abuja|work=The Nation|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channelstv.com/2014/11/14/police-rearrests-kogi-prison-break-escapee/|title=Police Rearrests Kogi Prison Break Escapee|work=Channels Television|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref>
==Incident== The incident was reported to have occurred on Sunday, 2 November 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.informationng.com/2014/11/kogi-jail-break-12-escaped-inmates-re-arrested.html|title=Kogi Jail Break: 12 Escaped Inmates Re-Arrested|author=daniel|work=INFORMATION NIGERIA|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> The attack was linked with [[Boko Haram|boko haram]], the Islamic insurgents in the northeastern [[Nigeria]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2014/11/kogi-jailbreak-moro-gives-ultimatum-contractor/|title=Kogi jailbreak: Moro gives ultimatum to contractor|work=Vanguard News|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> The comptroller-general of the [[Nigerian Prisons Services]], Alhaji Aminu Sule claimed that the prison break operation was successful as a result of poor funding of the [[Nigerian Prisons Services]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mynewswatchtimesng.com/kogi-jailbreak-need-improved-justice-prison-system/ |title=Kogi jailbreak: Need for improved justice, prison system |author=Cyril Mbah, Abuja |work=Newswatch Times |accessdate=24 December 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224215958/http://www.mynewswatchtimesng.com/kogi-jailbreak-need-improved-justice-prison-system/ |archivedate=24 December 2014 |df= }}</ref> that the prison cells were still the same old building since the prison's establishment in 1934.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://leadership.ng/news/389197/kogi-jail-break-gunmen-attack-prison-free-145-inmates|title=Kogi Jail Break: Gunmen Attack Prison, Free 145 Inmates - Nigerian News from Leadership Newspapers|work=Nigerian News from Leadership Newspapers|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref>
