'''Mass sexual assault''' is the collective [[sexual assault]] of women, and sometimes children, in public by groups of unrelated men. Typically acting under the protective cover of large gatherings, victims have reported being groped, stripped, beaten, bitten, penetrated and raped.<ref name="Barak 2003">{{cite book | last=Barak | first=Gregg | title=Violence and nonviolence pathways to understanding | publisher=SAGE Publications | location=Thousand Oaks, Calif | year=2003 | isbn=0-7619-2696-8 | pages=77–78}}</ref>

{{Violence against women}}

==Egypt==
{{see also|Mass sexual assault in Egypt}}
In Egypt, several mass sexual assaults have received wide international coverage. In [[Arabic]], the term "mass sexual assaults" translates as {{lang|ar| تحرش جماعي}} (''taḥarrush jamāʿī''), often incorrectly transliterated in the media<ref name=Shams21Jan2016>Shams, Alex (21 January 2016). [http://www.huffingtonpost.com/alex-shams/sexism-isnt-an-arab-cultural-practice_b_9022056.html "Neither Taharrush Gamea Nor Sexism Are Arab 'Cultural Practices'"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309150748/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/alex-shams/sexism-isnt-an-arab-cultural-practice_b_9022056.html |date=2017-03-09 }}, ''Huffington Post''.</ref> as "taharrush gamea" following a German police report into the 2016 [[New Year's Eve sexual assaults in Germany]].<ref name="Nordrhein-Westfalen report, 10 Jan 2016">[http://www.mik.nrw.de/fileadmin/user_upload/Redakteure/Dokumente/Themen_und_Aufgaben/Schutz_und_Sicherheit/160111ssia/160111berichtmik.pdf "Bericht des Ministeriums für Inneres und Kommunales über die Übergriffe am Hauptbahnhof Köln in der Silvesternacht"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160122032759/http://www.mik.nrw.de/fileadmin/user_upload/Redakteure/Dokumente/Themen_und_Aufgaben/Schutz_und_Sicherheit/160111ssia/160111berichtmik.pdf |date=2016-01-22 }}, Ministerium für Inneres und Kommunales des Landes Nordrhein-Westfalen, 10 January 2016, pp.&nbsp;1–15.</ref>{{rp|15}}

==Germany==
{{further|New Year's Eve sexual assaults in Germany}}
During [[New Year's Eve]] celebrations 2015/2016, incidents of mass sexual assault and numerous [[theft]]s occurred in [[Germany]], mainly in [[Cologne]] city center.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.faz.net/aktuell/politik/inland/koeln-meldet-inzwischen-106-anzeigen-nach-uebergriffen-an-silvester-14000124.html|title=Mehr als 100 Anzeigen nach Übergriffen an Silvester|trans-title=More than 100 reports of assaults on New Year's Eve|work=[[Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung]]|accessdate=24 January 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160125091915/http://www.faz.net/aktuell/politik/inland/koeln-meldet-inzwischen-106-anzeigen-nach-uebergriffen-an-silvester-14000124.html|archivedate=25 January 2016|df=}}{{de icon}}</ref>

==India==
{{see also|2012 Guwahati molestation case|2012 Mangalore homestay attack|Eve teasing|Blank Noise}}
Several cases of mass sexual assault have been reported in India. In July 2012, a teenage girl was sexually assaulted for up to 45 minutes by a large group of men outside a bar in Guwahati, Assam. No one intervened until the police arrived.<ref>Helen Pidd, [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/jul/15/india-media-sexual-assault-girl "Indian anger over media footage of girl being sexually assaulted"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202121200/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/jul/15/india-media-sexual-assault-girl |date=2017-02-02 }}, ''The Guardian'', 15 July 2012.</ref>

During the [[2002 riots in Gujarat]], targeted violence against Muslim women and children documented by civil society groups reported "mass rapes, live burials and burnings, acid attacks, impaling, and other brutal forms of torture that was deeply gendered, and linked violence against women with violence on their children – both born and unborn".<ref>{{cite book|last1=Jacob|first1=Cecilia|editor1-last=D'Costa|editor1-first=Bina|title=Children and Violence - Politics of Conflict in South Asia|date=October 2016|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|isbn=9781107117242|page=203|chapter=Children Affected by Political Violence in India}}</ref> Survivors reported "that sexual violence consisted of forced nudity, mass rapes, gang-rapes, mutilation, insertion of objects into bodies, cutting of breasts, slitting the stomach and reproductive organs, and carving of Hindu religious symbols on women's body parts.<ref name="Renu Khanna 2008">{{cite journal|last=Khanna|first=Renu|title=Communal Violence in Gujarat, India: Impact of Sexual Violence and Responsibilities of the Health Care System|journal=Reproductive Health Matters|year=2008|volume=16|issue=31|page=14|doi=10.1016/s0968-8080(08)31357-3}}
</ref> The Concerned Citizens' Tribunal, characterised the use of rape "as an instrument for the subjugation and humiliation of a community".<ref name="Renu Khanna 2008"/>

==Pakistan==
{{main|Rape in Pakistan}}
British television presenter [[Saira Khan]] said in 2016 that she had been sexually assaulted by a crowd in Pakistan in 2007 while filming a documentary for the BBC. She accused the BBC of having ignored the attack.<ref>[http://tribune.com.pk/story/1026680/apprentice-star-claims-she-was-sexually-assaulted-in-pakistan/ "Apprentice star claims she was sexually assaulted in Pakistan"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160210034722/http://tribune.com.pk/story/1026680/apprentice-star-claims-she-was-sexually-assaulted-in-pakistan/ |date=2016-02-10 }}, ''Express Tribune'', 13 January 2016.</ref>

==Sweden==
{{further|We Are Sthlm sexual assaults}}
Female participants at ''We Are Sthlm'', a summer music festival for teenagers in Stockholm, reported in 2014 and 2015 that they had been surrounded and molested by groups of males, mostly teenage boys. Police were accused of having failed to publicize the attacks because the suspects were mostly from Afghanistan. The incidents came to light only after the 2016 New Year's Eve attacks in Germany when the Stockholm Police were accused of covering up the incidents, which they denied.<ref>{{cite news|title=Assaults at the Stockholm festival have never been fully investigated|url=http://www.dn.se/nyheter/sverige/assaults-at-the-stockholm-festival-have-never-been-fully-investigated/|work=Dagens Nyheter|date=11 January 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160112031958/http://www.dn.se/nyheter/sverige/assaults-at-the-stockholm-festival-have-never-been-fully-investigated/|archivedate=12 January 2016|df=}}{{pb}}
