==United States==
{{further|Woodstock 1999|Puerto Rican Day Parade attacks|Seattle Mardi Gras riot}}
In July 1999 [[Woodstock 1999]] took place and Police subsequently investigated four complaints of sexual assault and rape, including digital rape, that allegedly occurred. At least one eyewitness, who was working as a volunteer at the event, reported to the [[Washington Post]] that he had seen a woman who was [[crowd surfing]] pulled down into the [[mosh pit]] and raped by five men.<ref>Alona Wartofsky, [https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/national/daily/july99/woodstock29.htm "Police Investigate Reports of Rapes at Woodstock"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120219071649/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/national/daily/july99/woodstock29.htm |date=2012-02-19 }}, ''The Washington Post'', 29 July 1999.</ref>

On 11 June 2000 at least 44 women reported being sexually assaulted and robbed by a group of 60 men during the [[Puerto Rican Day Parade]] in New York. The police were heavily criticized for their handling of the attacks.<ref>Michael Ellison, [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2000/jun/17/michaelellison1 "NY police 'ignored' park sex attacks"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202122506/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2000/jun/17/michaelellison1 |date=2017-02-02 }}, ''The Guardian'', 17 June 2000.</ref>

In  February 2001, witnesses saw groups of men [[grope]] women, tear off their clothes and apparently digitally penetrate them during the [[Mardi Gras]] celebrations in Seattle, Washington.<ref>{{cite news | first=Lewis | last=Kamb | author2=Tracy Johnson | title=Many sexual assaults at Mardi Gras | date=10 March 2001 | work=Seattle Post-Intelligencer | url=http://seattlep-i.nwsource.com/local/mardi10.shtml | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010312012137/http://seattlep-i.nwsource.com/local/mardi10.shtml | archive-date=12 March 2001 }}{{pb}}
{{cite news|title=Mardi Gras news photo that wasn't published wins prize|url=http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=20020331&slug=photo31m|date=31 March 2002|newspaper=The Seattle Times|author=Davila, Florangela|author2=Ostrom, Carol M.|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110219103859/http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=20020331&slug=photo31m|archivedate=19 February 2011|df=}}{{pb}}
{{cite news | url=http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=20010302&slug=dead02m0 | title=Man Killed at Mardi Gras was trying to help woman | date=2 March 2001 | work=The Seattle Times | first1=Ian | last1=Ith | first2=Nancy | last2=Bartley | deadurl=no | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101209183410/http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=20010302&slug=dead02m0 | archivedate=9 December 2010 | df= }}</ref>

==Vietnam==
In July 2015, there were allegations that at least 20 [[Women in Vietnam|girls or women at the Ho Tay water park in Hanoi, Vietnam]] were reportedly sexually assaulted by a group of more than 70 men who assaulted, scratched and inappropriately touched them.<ref>
Water Park’s alleged mass sexual assault under scrutiny, {{cite web |url=https://news.yahoo.com/water-park-alleged-mass-sexual-assault-under-scrutiny-113414092.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2017-01-14 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160321030755/http://news.yahoo.com/water-park-alleged-mass-sexual-assault-under-scrutiny-113414092.html |archivedate=2016-03-21 |df= }}</ref> Men groped the women and tore their bikinis from their bodies, and Vietnamese officials blamed the women for being attacked. Bystanders ignored the women while they were assaulted, and people cheered and applauded the men who posted photos of themselves assaulting the women on Facebook.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.360nobs.com/2015/07/dozens-of-men-strip-finger-and-sexually-assault-women-in-overcrowded-water-park-photos/|title=Dozens Of Men Strip, Finger And Sexually Assault Women In Overcrowded Water Park (Photos)|work=360Nobs.com|accessdate=21 May 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160507145627/https://www.360nobs.com/2015/07/dozens-of-men-strip-finger-and-sexually-assault-women-in-overcrowded-water-park-photos/|archivedate=7 May 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://elitedaily.com/news/world/sexual-assault-vietnam-waterpark/1105802/|title=20 Or More Women Were Sexually Assaulted At A Vietnam Water Park And Nobody Seems To Care|date=14 July 2015|work=Elite Daily|accessdate=21 May 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216153909/http://elitedaily.com/news/world/sexual-assault-vietnam-waterpark/1105802/|archivedate=16 February 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://redwiretimes.com/letters/men-strip-finger-and-molest-bikini-clad-girls-at-waterpark-after-being-given-free-entry/|title=Men Strip, "Finger" and Molest Bikini-Clad Girls at Water Park after Being Given Free Entry - RedWire Times Singapore -  RedWire Times Singapore|work=RedWire Times Singapore|accessdate=21 May 2016|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive